 among communities. By harnessing these alternative ways of being, food aid and communities can be part of movements for economic and racial justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aDiscriminationzGreat Britain. 0aFood reliefxPolitical aspectszGreat Britain. 0aFood reliefxSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aPoorzGreat Britain. 0aPovertyxSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 0aRacismzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh1 aPickett, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311119677040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447358572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447358572/original  a978-3-11-119677-0  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles